On December 17, 1903, the Wright Brothers made the first successful manned flight in a powered aircraft. To commemorate this achievement, December 17th is designated as Wright Brothers Day. The proclamation recognizes the contributions of aviation to the nation and the world, and emphasizes the importance of aviation in connecting people, commerce, and industry. The proclamation also highlights the commitment of the administration to ensure that the United States remains a leader in aviation and aerospace innovation. The proclamation concludes by officially declaring December 17, 2019, as Wright Brothers Day.